==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intuitionalism
<hw>In`tu*i"tion*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The doctrine that the perception or
recognition of primary truth is intuitive, or direct and immediate; --
opposed to <contr>sensationalism</contr>, and
<contr>experientialism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intuitionalist</ent>⟦br⟧
